content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a solution.

The target image shows two separate structures:

Left Structure:
- Base layer: Blue cube (block 6) and green cube (block 7)
- Middle layer: Yellow horizontal block (block 9) 
- Top layer: Orange triangular block (block 15)
- Additional red cube (block 5) next to the structure

Right Structure:
- Bottom layer: Four red arch blocks forming a base (blocks 1, 2, 3, 4)
- Middle layer: Yellow horizontal blocks (blocks 9, 10) spanning across the arches
- Top layer: Red arch blocks (blocks 1, 2) creating upper tunnels

Assembly Instructions:
{
Step1: Move block with index 6 // Blue cube base left
Step2: Move block with index 7 // Green cube base left
Step3: Move block with index 9 // Yellow horizontal block on left structure
Step4: Move block with index 15 // Orange triangle on top left
Step5: Move block with index 5 // Red cube beside left structure
Step6: Move block with index 1 // Bottom right structure front left arch
Step7: Move block with index 2 // Bottom right structure front right arch
Step8: Move block with index 3 // Bottom right structure back left arch
Step9: Move block with index 4 // Bottom right structure back right arch
Step10: Move block with index 9 // First yellow horizontal block on right structure
Step11: Move block with index 10 // Second yellow horizontal block on right structure
Step12: Move block with index 1 // Top right structure front arch
Step13: Move block with index 2 // Top right structure back arch
}
